      "label": "Transcript",
      "value": "Charleston April 12th. 1833.\nDear Sister,\nI intended to set out last Tuesday the 9th for Pendleton, but I was taken sick on Monday, and I am now in bed with a fever. I cannot fix upon any time for my journey until I am better, but I still propose to go as if I am well enough. I remain, dear Sister,\nAffectionately yours\nC. [Charlotte] Manigault\n[end of page one]\n[written vertically in the center of the page]\n[in different ink] 1834\n[stamp] Charleston S.C. [South Carolina] April 15\nMiss Henrietta A. Drayton\nPendleton Village\nSouth Carolina.\n[End of page two]"
